<br>
Last night, I played my weekly (that's right -- I play only once a week) session on FV and was pleasantly surprised that FV had fewer players on it during prime time than E'ci -- my main server.<br>
<br>
Without any hard evidence either way, it seems that the tide has shifted towards the RP side and against the d00ds.  Why?  I don't really know.  Maybe its because of the Trivial Loot Code, which can affect later quest items (i.e.  If you don't take out Squire Narls in EC at the appropriate level, you'll never be able to get the Soulfire sword; the alternative of relying on others to get you Narls' head is too time consuming).  Maybe its because unless you and some of your friends started out at the same time, and played for the same amount of time, you are now too high to help them out significantly.<br>
<br>
The reason . . . well whatever the reason its not important.  I just found it interesting that FV has dropped in population in such a relatively short period of time.<br>
<br>
Maedhros<br>
Druid, 4th Circle<br>
